Annotations

ah <- AnnotationHub() %>%
    subset(species == "Mus musculus") %>%
    subset(dataprovider == "Ensembl") %>%
    subset(genome == "GRCm39") %>% # GRCm39 is relative new release 104 is not out yet
    subset(rdataclass == "EnsDb")
ensDb <- ah[["AH89457"]]
grTrans <- transcripts(ensDb)
trLengths <- exonsBy(ensDb, "tx") %>%
  width() %>%
  vapply(sum, integer(1))
mcols(grTrans)$length <- trLengths[names(grTrans)]

Similarly to the Quality Assessment steps, GRanges objects were formed at the gene and transcript levels, to enable estimation of GC content and length for each transcript and gene. GC content and transcript length are available for each transcript, and for gene-level estimates, GC content was taken as the sum of all GC bases divided by the sum of all transcript lengths, effectively averaging across all transcripts. Gene length was defined as the median transcript length.

gcGene <- grTrans %>%
  mcols() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  dplyr::select(gene_id, tx_id, gc_content, length, tx_name) %>%
  as_tibble() %>%
  group_by(gene_id) %>%
  summarise(
    gc_content = sum(gc_content*length) / sum(length),
    length = ceiling(median(length)),)

grGenes <- genes(ensDb)
mcols(grGenes) %<>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  left_join(gcGene) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  DataFrame()

Sample metadata was also loaded

setwd("C:/Users/cronos/Box Sync/Desktop/Renal Hypertrophy/CRH_RNAseq")

samples <- read_csv("samples.csv") %>%
  distinct(sampleName, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  dplyr::select(sample = sampleName,time= timepoint, everything()) %>%
  mutate(
    treatment = factor(treatment, levels = c("Sham", "Unx")),
    time = factor(time, levels=c("24hr","48hr","72hr")),
    group = factor(group, 
                       levels=c("Sham.24hr", "Sham.48hr", "Sham.72hr", 
                                "Unx.24hr", "Unx.48hr", "Unx.72hr")))

groupCols <- samples$group %>%
  levels() %>%
  length() %>%
  brewer.pal("Dark2") %>%
  setNames(levels(samples$group))

timeCols <- samples$time %>%
  levels() %>%
  length() %>%
  brewer.pal("Set2") %>%
  setNames(levels(samples$time))

treatCols <- samples$treatment %>%
  levels() %>%
  length() %>%
  brewer.pal("Set1") %>%
  setNames(levels(samples$treatment)) %>%
  .[-3]

samples %>%  
  kable %>%

Mark genes that are stable

#Mark stable sham genes in topTable
topTables_stable <- topTables[1:3] %>%
  sapply(function(x){
    x %>% as.data.frame() %>% 
      mutate(Stable = case_when(gene_id %in% stable_in_sham & DE == TRUE ~ TRUE),
      Stable = ifelse(is.na(Stable), "FALSE", Stable))}, simplify = FALSE)

Top 20 from each group for boxplot

# select some genes for plotting
out1 <- topTables_stable$Sham24vsUnx24 %>% dplyr::filter(DE==TRUE, Stable==TRUE) %>% dplyr::slice(1:20)
out2 <- topTables_stable$Sham48vsUnx48 %>% dplyr::filter(DE==TRUE, Stable==TRUE) %>% dplyr::slice(1:20)

cpm(dgeList, log=TRUE, prior.count = 3)[combined,] %>% 
  head(.,n=100) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column("gene_id") %>%
    as_tibble() %>%
    gather(key = "sample", value = "CPM", -gene_id) %>%
    mutate(CPM = CPM + 1) %>%
    left_join(dgeList$samples) %>%
  mutate(treatment = fct_relevel(treatment, "Sham","Unx")) %>%
  mutate(group = fct_relevel(group, "Sham.24hr","Sham.48hr","Sham.72hr","Unx.24hr","Unx.48hr","Unx.72hr")) %>%
    ggplot(aes(group, CPM, fill = treatment)) +
  geom_point() +
    # geom_text_repel(aes(label = time)) +
  stat_boxplot(geom='errorbar', linetype=1, width=0.5)+
    geom_boxplot() +
    facet_wrap(
        ~gene_id, 
        scales = "free_y", 
        labeller = as_labeller(
            structure(dgeList$genes$gene_name, names = dgeList$genes$gene_id)
        )) + scale_fill_manual(values = treatCols) +
    scale_y_log10()  +
    labs(x = "Treatment Group",
         y = "CPM + 1") +
    theme(legend.position = "none",axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90), 
          strip.text = element_text(size= 10, face="bold"))

GO Enrichment Analysis

minPath <- 4
goSummaries <- url("https://uofabioinformaticshub.github.io/summaries2GO/data/goSummaries.RDS") %>%
    readRDS() %>%
    dplyr::rename(go_id = id)

A very brief enrichment analysis was then performed using the default settings of the function goana(). As goana relies on entrezgene identifiers, analysis was switched to these IDs for this step of the analysis. Results were then limited to GO terms with at least 4 steps back the root terms for each ontology.

orgDb <- org.Mm.eg.db
sigIDs <- topTables_stable$Sham48vsUnx48 %>%
    dplyr::filter(adj.P.Val < 0.05 & Status=="Up" & Stable==TRUE) %>%
    extract2("entrezid") %>%
    unlist() %>%
  na.omit() %>%
    unique()
uv <- unlist(topTables_stable$Sham48vsUnx48$entrezid) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  unique()
goRes <- goana.default(sigIDs, universe = uv, species = "Mm") %>%
    rownames_to_column("go_id") %>%
    dplyr::rename(ontology = Ont) %>%
    as_tibble() %>%
    dplyr::filter(DE > 0) %>%
    left_join(goSummaries)

A total of 8,569 GO terms were identified amongst the differentially expressed genes.

goRes %>%
    dplyr::filter(shortest_path > minPath) %>%
    mutate(adjP = p.adjust(P.DE, "bonferroni"),
           FDR = p.adjust(P.DE, "fdr")) %>%
    arrange(ontology, P.DE) %>%
    dplyr::filter(FDR < 0.05) %>%
    mutate(Expected_DE = round(length(sigIDs) * N / length(uv), 1)) %>%
    dplyr::select(`GO ID` = go_id, Term, Ontology = ontology, N, Obs_DE = DE, Expected_DE, P.DE, FDR) %>%
    pander(caption = "*Significantly enriched GO terms using a FDR-adjusted p-value < 0.05 as the criteria for significance*",
           split.tables = Inf)

go2Drop <- dplyr::filter(goSummaries, shortest_path <= minPath)$go_id
